-- Blackstone-backed Travelport's shares rise 10.6 pct in debut
-- By Avik Das in Bangalore
-- Thu Sep 25, 2014 10:02AM EDT
-- None



Sept 25 (Reuters) - Travelport Worldwide Ltd's <TVPT.N> shares rose as much as 10.6 percent in their market debut, valuing the provider of booking and payment services to the travel industry at about $2.13 billion.

The company, backed by Blackstone Group LP <BX.N>, raised about $480 million after its offering of 30 million shares was priced at $16 per share, the top end of the expected range of $14-$16. [ID:nL3N0RP639] Travelport, which provides a travel commerce platform and technology services to travel agents, airlines, hotels and car rental companies, sold all of the shares on offer. The stock opened at $17.69 and touched a high of $17.70.